  &lt;li&gt;The adverbs and the adjectives in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adjectives tell us something about a person or a thing. Adjectives can modify nouns (here: girl) or pronouns (here: she).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adverbs tell us in what way someone does something. Adverbs can modify verbs (here: drive), adjectives or other adverbs.&lt;/p&gt;

