  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">The adverbs and the adjectives in English</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Adjetives</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/jekyll/update/2018/02/18/adjetives.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Adjetives" /><published>2018-02-18T22:10:19+01:00</published><updated>2018-02-18T22:10:19+01:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/jekyll/update/2018/02/18/adjetives</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/jekyll/update/2018/02/18/adjetives.html">&lt;p&gt;We use adjectives to describe nouns.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most adjectives can be used in front of a noun.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Examples: 
They have a beautiful house.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We saw a very exciting film last night.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or after a link verb like be, look or feel:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Their house is beautiful.
That film looks interesting.&lt;/p&gt;

